# {projectName} Workspace

This is the delivery workspace for **{projectName}**.

Refer to `AGENTS.md` for the full repo layout, key documents, and conventions.

## Required reading

Before starting any task, you **MUST** read:

- `AGENTS.md` -- repo layout, key documents, conventions
- `product/product.md` -- product strategy and requirements
- `product/roadmap.md` -- phased roadmap
- `architecture/solution.md` -- solution architecture
- `architecture/decisions/register.md` -- architecture decision records
- `docs/conventions/definition-of-ready.md` -- when a story is ready to implement
- `docs/conventions/definition-of-done.md` -- when a story is actually done

These documents contain decisions and patterns that override general knowledge.

## Repositories

| Repo | Role |
|------|------|
| `{project}-space` (this repo) | Delivery artifacts: product, architecture, backlog, epics, reports |
| `{project}` (`../{project}`) | Application code |

## Skills

Delivery activity skills are provided by `@daddia/skills` and discovered automatically from `.cursor/skills/`. Skills include prompts for requirements writing, technical design, ADRs, code review, and more. Type `/` to see available skills.

## Conventions

- All delivery artifacts are Markdown with YAML frontmatter
- Epic artifacts go in `work/{EPIC_ID}/`
- Architecture decisions follow the template at `architecture/decisions/adr-template.md`
- This workspace contains no application code -- that belongs in the `{project}` repo
